<span> With these numbers, France, which has the highest life expectancy in the EU for women (85.2 years in 2022), was the country with more centennials in Europe last year. Their profile, "is often that of a woman who has done work in the open air rather laborious - peasant, farmer's wife - and who has had a power based on healthy and unturned products", explained Laurent Toussaint, specialist in supercentennials and co-conductor of the blog "Les grands centenaires francais". The alleged older French woman, Marie-Rose Tessier, who lives in a nursing home in Les Sables-d'Olonne, in Vandea, will celebrate her 114 birthday on 21 May. Jeanne Calment, who died at 122 in 1997, is the longest person in history, according to Guinness World Records. On a global level, the allegedly older person is Maria Branyas Morera, born in the United States and resident in Spain, who is 117 years old, according to the Californian organization GRG (Gerontology Research Group). </span
